      "amount": "carrot"
    },
    {
      "name": "2 tablespoons soy sauce",
      "amount": "tablespoons"
    },
    {
      "name": "2 tablespoons rice vinegar",
      "amount": "tablespoons"
    },
    {
      "name": "2 eggs, beaten",
      "amount": "set"
    },
    {
      "name": "1 cup egg yolks",
      "amount": "cup"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the tofu and cook until golden brown on both sides. Remove from pan and set aside.",
    "In the same pan, add fermented black beans, minced garlic, lime juice, and soy sauce. Stir to combine.",
    "Add the bell peppers and carrot. Cook for about 2 minutes or until slightly softened.",
    "Pour in the beaten eggs and stir-fry quickly until cooked through but not fully set.",
    "Fold in the egg yolks gently to incorporate with the other ingredients. Taste and adjust seasoning if needed.",
    "Serve hot as a snack alongside steamed rice or noodles."
